review_blob: This beer has a strong pumpkin kick and is perfect for the autumn season. Its a dedicated must on a cool October night.
Very strong. Not much flavor but still a decent drink. I shouldve ordered the Shipyard.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Decent beer. Mediocre flavour with an average overall taste. Definitely not my first choice, but again, decent and I wouldnt turn down a bottle.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: In my opinion, this is the best cider beer out there. It beats your Redds and Angry Orchards by packing a wallop of apple with slight bitter finish. This is a contestant, smooth brew across the palate. Wow!
What a great beer! This copper tinted brew blends earthy aromatics with a perfect hoppy, caramel  taste. Yum!
beer_name: Inlet Brewing Monk in the Trunk Organic Amber Ale

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: A medium colour of caramel pairs with basement aromas to bring this lovely beer together as one of the best overall semi mainstream beers. Yum
This is a black IPA and what I would call a stout. Still, this is a very smooth beer and definitely worth a try.
Not the greatest of beers. Semi-sweet but a very basic flavour.I wouldnt order this beer again yet Im glad I tried it.
Not bad. Very smooth and an easy drink. Henrys is lighter of most lagers. You can drink this on any occasion.
Very light Summery beer! I love the flavor and citrus notes. Definitely one of my favorites.

A very mellow amber color and a malty, caramel aroma combine to make a smooth Pale Ale. Stones is a simple beer with simple ingredients, no preservatives, and a high ABV. You cant go wrong with this one.

Im definitely a fan of the Whites, and a beer like the Harpoons Unfiltered Offering (UFO) is an example why. The aroma is that of orange with a faint pop of spices while the unfiltered taste is clean and well blended. Definitely a one up on your Blue Moons and Shock Tops!

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A name like Leinenkugels makes one think of interesting flavors and unique palates. Unfortunately, the Lemon Berry Shandy is at the shallow end of the flavor pool. This beer lacks complexity and does a poor job in cohesion of flavors. Yuk!
